Text.Value: I mean, I didn't say that...
Sure. I'm calm. Calm as can be. Turns out glass number five was rather soothing.
I can't help but notice you're drinking anyway, Dave.
You are incorrigible today.
Well, if the wine's here already, I might as well drink it.
What do you mean?
This is a welcome distraction from all the war talk.
You do get very negative after a couple of glasses.
No, we're being too lax right now.
Can you please calm down?
You saw what happened. Our lives are at risk and you're asking me to calm down?
Especially at her age. Isn't she a bit old to be cutting about a wine festival?
The streets were packed. The stench was... potent.
I wish you hadn't said anything.
Are we a bit calmer now, pal?
Quite the turnout, don't you think?
Thank gods.
So you think they shouldn't bring any more wine? That right?
Why not? It's good to relax.
These refugees are killers, apparently. And they're everywhere.
You should've seen the cheese festival last year.
The only killer around here is going to be your hangover tomorrow, Dave.
Anyway - what are we supposed to do if that bastard comes back? When will Gortash fix things?
I just think we shouldn't be letting our guard down.
My, that halfling lady is lucky to be here.
Refugees, wine festivals, we're wasting our resources.
All I'm saying is she's old. The maniac couldn't have tried very hard.
If she's lived to be that old in Baldur's Gate, she deserves a glass of wine or six. Lighten up.

Synopsis: When the Wine Festival begins, some ADs will be playing in row. This is one of them.
